# Documentation Standards Self-Update

Meta-rules for triggering updates when documentation standards themselves change.

<rule>
name: documentation_standards_self_update
description: Trigger updates when documentation standards themselves change
filters:
  # Changes to documentation standards
  - type: file_extension
    pattern: "\\.cursor/rules/.*\\.mdc"
  # Changes to AI instructions
  - type: file_extension
    pattern: "\\.github/instructions/.*\\.instructions\\.md"

actions:
  - type: suggest
    message: |
      Documentation Meta-Update Required:

      Changes to documentation standards or AI instructions detected.

      **Review and update:**
      - Ensure all documentation files reference current standards
      - Update any examples or templates that reference changed rules
      - Verify trigger patterns match current project structure
      - Check that priority levels and versioning are consistent

      **Files to review:**
      - All documentation files that reference these standards
      - README.md sections about contributing and documentation
      - Any templates or examples that use these patterns

metadata:
  priority: medium
  version: 1.0
</rule>
